Current version of Foundation is there, but expanded to include v.3 and
v.4 documentation links. Version 3 can be quite helpful for someone
starting with this Framework as it is more verbose and the switch
between code and example is easy to 'catch'.
Gumby is yet another framework and has some nifty features.

Can remove Github links for less popular frameworks if you want to keep them minor. But wanted main frameworks (angular, backbone, etc) to be consistent.
